This paper focuses on improving end-users productivity in spreadsheets, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of a model-driven engineering approach also suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the study involves analyzing data in spreadsheets, which could relate to database systems (cs.DB) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
